The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 23 March is 41,205 (4,769.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 March, there were 292 new confirmed cases (33.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 March, there were 290 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 1% (2 extra cases).
